|s@i si starebbe un cane intra due dame~: The third
example returns to the case of equal desire, rather than fear,
now on the part of a hunting dog at equal distance between two
does.  |dame~: The word is obsolete in the sense in which Dante
uses it here.  Cf. the Latin ^damma~ and the modern Italian
^daina.~
