|Per che, s'ella~... |forza~: Clearly Beatrice
means that if the flame remains bent over when the wind has
ceased, then it "follows" the violence or compulsion from
without.  |ella~: The will.  |e cos@i queste~: And thus did
Piccarda and Constance, who, when free of compulsion from
without, when no longer detained outside the convent by
compulsion, could have returned to the cloister.  Thus their will
was not ^intero~ (vs. 82), as implied by the following verse; or,
to keep the metaphor of the flame, they remained "bent" by the
violence, a point that must now be dealt with (vss. 91-114).
